    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Indianism is a current that started in Brazilian romantic literature (c.1836 - c.1881) and later in painting, in which Indian figures were idealized and represented as symbols of a nationality.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
